WEBVTT

00:09.576 --> 00:11.678
I just want
to tell you guys something.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.748
Deneia:
Nothing bad, I hope.

00:14.848 --> 00:16.649
- Yeah.
- Come on.

00:18.685 --> 00:22.022
I mean, it's no secret that
Karen and I had a connection.

00:22.088 --> 00:25.025
And so her not being here --

00:25.091 --> 00:29.896
It doesn't make much sense
to me to stick around.

00:29.996 --> 00:33.199
- Oh, come on.
- Oh.

00:35.368 --> 00:38.171
Perhaps Karen and I can find
a way to reconnect

00:38.238 --> 00:39.706
and kind of figure that out.

00:39.773 --> 00:42.208
You know, I'm very interested
in pursuing that.

00:42.275 --> 00:43.843
So that's
what I'm gonna do.

00:43.910 --> 00:46.279
You're a good man.

00:46.379 --> 00:48.948
And I'm glad to meet you, and
now I know that there's men out

00:49.049 --> 00:53.953
there that are amazing fathers,
and it gives me hope.

00:54.054 --> 00:56.056
I got to stay away
from her because she...

00:58.091 --> 01:00.026
That was really nice.
Thank you.

01:00.093 --> 01:02.028
I've gotten what I think

01:02.095 --> 01:04.097
I was supposed to get
from coming here.

01:04.197 --> 01:06.466
Actually, I've gotten that
and a hell of a lot more.

01:06.566 --> 01:07.901
Bye.

01:07.967 --> 01:09.402
- Bye, Troy.
- Bye, Troy.

01:09.469 --> 01:11.404
- See you on the backside.
- We love you.

01:11.471 --> 01:14.307
I feel whole and complete
about the connections

01:14.407 --> 01:16.209
that I've made
with my new friends,

01:16.276 --> 01:17.544
and certainly with Karen.

01:17.610 --> 01:18.945
Thank you, Scotty.

01:19.045 --> 01:20.313
You got it, Petrick.

01:20.413 --> 01:22.048
I can see myself
falling in love with Karen.

01:22.115 --> 01:24.417
And so I'm just ready
to -- to move forward

01:24.484 --> 01:26.486
and take the next step
towards that.

01:41.768 --> 01:45.505
Leaving the house,
I know it's the right decision,

01:45.605 --> 01:48.608
but it's just bittersweet
to leave these great people.

01:48.675 --> 01:53.313
And I'm also unbelievably
excited to see Noah

01:53.413 --> 01:56.349
and see how he is
and how things have been going.

02:04.791 --> 02:06.359
- It's your dad.
- Your dad is here, bro.

02:06.459 --> 02:09.195
Hey.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.833
Oh.

02:13.933 --> 02:15.702
Whoa!

02:15.802 --> 02:16.936
Hey, guy.

02:17.003 --> 02:18.338
How you doing, man?

02:18.438 --> 02:19.606
It's nice to see you.

02:19.672 --> 02:21.374
It's freaking me out
seeing you a little bit.

02:21.474 --> 02:23.209
I feel like
you've gotten bigger.

02:23.309 --> 02:25.945
The fact that my dad is
leaving Second Chance Retreat,

02:26.012 --> 02:28.014
it means I'm going home.

02:28.114 --> 02:30.216
I feel upset about it.

02:30.316 --> 02:32.685
But whatever my dad
needs from me, I'll do.

02:32.785 --> 02:34.888
So, Dad,
how was your thing, bro?

02:34.988 --> 02:36.022
How you been?

02:36.122 --> 02:37.323
- How's your thing?
- Yeah.

02:37.390 --> 02:38.791
I don't know
if you noticed.

02:38.858 --> 02:40.860
I kind of actually already
know the answer to that.

02:40.960 --> 02:42.629
Oh, my God!
Look at that.

02:42.695 --> 02:44.564
Yeah. Yeah.

02:44.664 --> 02:45.698
Dude, you don't understand.

02:45.798 --> 02:47.534
14 hours a day,
we watch you.

02:47.634 --> 02:49.569
I know everything about you.

02:49.669 --> 02:51.704
And now I see you
in a whole different light.

02:51.804 --> 02:53.206
I don't even know
if you're my dad anymore.

02:53.306 --> 02:55.175
Okay, that's weird.

02:55.241 --> 02:57.377
This thing. You guys.
Yeah. Okay.

02:57.477 --> 02:59.078
Okay, now it's starting
to make sense.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.580
But I'm like,

03:00.680 --> 03:04.217
"So you guys have heard
everything, seen everything."

03:04.317 --> 03:07.253
And part of me is like,
"I mean,<i> everything</i> everything?"

03:07.353 --> 03:09.422
What's been going on
since I got here?

03:09.522 --> 03:14.093
We've been spying on you guys
and meddling and manipulating

03:14.194 --> 03:16.863
all the different
relationships in the house.

03:16.930 --> 03:20.533
So that means I actually
screwed up plenty with you.

03:20.600 --> 03:21.935
So you were the reason

03:22.035 --> 03:23.903
I kept getting never picked
in the beginning?

03:25.038 --> 03:26.206
It's like on "The Truman Show"

03:26.272 --> 03:27.607
when he opens a door
and he's like,

03:27.707 --> 03:29.442
"Oh, shit, I'm on a movie set."

03:29.542 --> 03:31.945
I mean, that's kind of
how it felt a little bit like.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.780
I-I always had this feeling

03:33.880 --> 03:36.049
I was like a rat trapped
in a maze,

03:36.115 --> 03:37.450
and it turns out I kind of was.

03:37.550 --> 03:39.085
And they were the ones
moving the cheese around.

03:39.185 --> 03:40.720
I'm like, "What is going on
with all this stuff?"

03:40.787 --> 03:42.288
Yeah, the Jimmy date.

03:42.388 --> 03:43.556
That was our fault.

03:43.623 --> 03:45.758
We messed up, bro.
We did not think.

03:45.858 --> 03:48.628
When Jimmy first started
third-wheeling your guys' date,

03:48.728 --> 03:50.797
we were laughing our asses
off.

03:50.897 --> 03:53.800
The apartment complex
I'm staying in, the alarm

03:53.900 --> 03:56.135
went off
at 5:00 a.m. today.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.271
What?

04:00.940 --> 04:02.041
Would it be, like, so rude

04:02.108 --> 04:04.043
if I just had, like,
a taste of that?

04:04.110 --> 04:05.812
Yes, because this
is, like, our date.

04:05.912 --> 04:09.749
You guys are responsible
for that debacle. Okay.

04:09.816 --> 04:13.386
Dad, it was unbearable, dude.
And I was like, "No, no!"

04:13.453 --> 04:16.456
It went a long ways towards --
A lot of my anxiety, too,

04:16.556 --> 04:18.324
about everything that's been
happening was kind of relieved

04:18.424 --> 04:21.561
in a weird way.
It was like, "Oh, I get it."

04:21.628 --> 04:24.497
Karen leaving abruptly
was, like, a big shock.

04:24.597 --> 04:25.798
I don't want to pull you
out of here

04:25.898 --> 04:27.166
'cause it sounds like
you guys

04:27.267 --> 04:28.668
are all really close friends
and everything,

04:28.768 --> 04:30.937
but there's nothing else
for me to pursue here,

04:31.004 --> 04:34.340
and so, yeah,
time to head out.

04:34.440 --> 04:38.845
Alex:
If Troy's journey was over,
that meant Noah's was, so...

04:38.945 --> 04:42.515
I was expecting it,
but something inside of me

04:42.615 --> 04:48.488
is hoping that something happens
to where he stays.

04:48.588 --> 04:50.456
I'm hopeful that actually,
though,

04:50.523 --> 04:53.459
there'll be a chance for Karen
and I to kind of reunite.

04:53.526 --> 04:55.695
Sooner rather than later,
in fact.

04:55.795 --> 04:59.098
Right? So sounds like
you guys concur, so...

04:59.165 --> 05:02.435
Yeah. Absolutely.

05:02.502 --> 05:04.937
So these guys are great,
but, you know,

05:05.004 --> 05:06.372
I think it's time
for them to do their thing,

05:06.472 --> 05:08.775
and you and I
are gonna go do our thing,

05:08.841 --> 05:11.311
and that's the way it goes
sometimes in life.

05:11.377 --> 05:13.546
But, I mean, the people
that are gonna stick with you

05:13.646 --> 05:15.214
are gonna stick
with you in this.

05:15.315 --> 05:16.683
I don't know how much
you guys heard,

05:16.783 --> 05:18.384
but it's one of the greatest
joys in my life.

05:18.484 --> 05:19.686
And then you get
to be my age

05:19.786 --> 05:21.354
and all of our age,
and it's like,

05:21.454 --> 05:22.822
"God, those are treasures
in your life."

05:22.889 --> 05:24.557
That's it.
That's what it's all about.

05:24.657 --> 05:25.892
- Yeah.
- Absolutely.

05:25.992 --> 05:28.061
So, I don't know
why I'm so emotional.

05:28.161 --> 05:30.029
You guys are...

05:30.129 --> 05:32.699
I'm definitely grateful
for the Second Chance Retreat

05:32.799 --> 05:37.403
because it helped my dad move on
from being a parent to,

05:37.503 --> 05:39.906
you know, being someone who has
a successful dating life.

05:40.006 --> 05:43.976
It allowed him to really
take that next step,

05:44.043 --> 05:45.845
and I'll cherish it.

05:45.912 --> 05:46.979
Favorite what?

05:51.517 --> 05:52.652
Woman:
Or is this real time?

05:52.719 --> 05:53.820
Oh, this is
a real-life Meddle?

05:57.423 --> 05:59.659
Oh, no.

05:59.726 --> 06:01.928
All right, Dad,
be careful with this, man.

06:02.028 --> 06:05.098
Yeah, obviously. I've been
on the other side of it.

06:05.198 --> 06:07.233
Okay. "Troy, you will now get

06:07.333 --> 06:11.003
to experience
your very own Meddle."

06:11.070 --> 06:13.039
Okay.

06:13.106 --> 06:15.575
"You must choose any two parents
to be interrupted

06:15.675 --> 06:18.745
by the Second Chance
Retreat sprinklers."

06:18.845 --> 06:21.114
Ohh, man.

06:21.214 --> 06:23.416
It's gonna come up. Oh, no.
I'm gonna have to watch it.

06:23.516 --> 06:26.119
Oh, God.
Ohh, man.

06:26.219 --> 06:28.254
Okay, to pick....

06:28.354 --> 06:30.757
"Who do you choose?"
You know what?

06:30.857 --> 06:34.794
So -- Okay,
so let's do your dad because

06:34.894 --> 06:37.029
he's just gonna go with it.

06:37.096 --> 06:39.298
And you know what? Let's do Kiki
because you know what?

06:39.399 --> 06:40.900
She'll just start dancing.

06:40.967 --> 06:43.536
I mean, I think
they'll see the joy in it.

06:43.603 --> 06:47.240
I choose Philip and Kiki to get
wet in the sprinklers.

06:47.306 --> 06:48.741
This is actually kind of fun.

06:48.808 --> 06:51.811
It'll be like,
"This is nice."

06:51.911 --> 06:53.746
Songs that I like
or what song speaks to me,

06:53.813 --> 06:56.149
so...I like karaoke,
and I love dancing, too.

06:56.249 --> 06:59.252
So any time I can get a chance
to dance, I'm down for it.

06:59.318 --> 07:02.321
Oh, no. They're having
a lovely conversation.

07:02.422 --> 07:03.990
Yeah, this is
how it goes, man.

07:04.090 --> 07:06.592
This is so weird.

07:06.659 --> 07:09.162
- Oh.
- Activated. All right.

07:11.264 --> 07:12.999
I can't believe
I'm part of this.

07:13.099 --> 07:16.002
The ground, the clouds
come in really fast.

07:16.102 --> 07:17.336
It moves so fast.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.505
I don't --
You know what I saw?

07:19.605 --> 07:21.674
I saw -- Oh. Okay.

07:25.745 --> 07:26.913
I think we're good.
Hey.

07:26.979 --> 07:28.514
I knew she'd like it.

07:31.751 --> 07:34.353
Ahh.
That is good.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.355
I think we want to probably
take a seat over here.

07:36.456 --> 07:37.623
You okay?

07:37.690 --> 07:39.192
I'm fine. Thank you.

07:39.292 --> 07:41.194
Maybe we should get a little
paper towel or something.

07:41.294 --> 07:43.529
Oh, okay. Yeah.
We should.

07:43.629 --> 07:46.499
Oh, man.
I feel terrible now.

07:46.599 --> 07:48.034
Aw.

07:48.134 --> 07:49.602
Please don't.
He'll be fine.

07:51.003 --> 07:53.272
Well, a lot of power you guys
had over here.

07:53.339 --> 07:56.943
That's freaking me out
a little bit, but...cool.

07:57.009 --> 07:58.711
Well, man...

07:58.811 --> 08:02.048
I got to see
what you guys have been up to.

08:02.148 --> 08:03.382
You ready to head out?

08:03.483 --> 08:06.686
Yeah. I probably should pack.
But...

08:06.786 --> 08:09.622
man, it's gonna be
an awkward goodbye, dude.

08:09.689 --> 08:12.225
Let's hug it out.

08:18.664 --> 08:22.401
Overall, I know that me
and the other kids in the house

08:22.502 --> 08:23.903
when our parents got divorced,

08:24.003 --> 08:27.206
we all kind of suffered
very similar consequences.

08:27.306 --> 08:29.242
- Love you, man.
- Nice meeting you.

08:29.342 --> 08:30.643
I can't believe
your Scott's kid.

08:30.710 --> 08:31.744
I know, right?

08:31.844 --> 08:33.212
Noah:
Being at this retreat,

08:33.312 --> 08:35.815
we have created
such a strong bond together.

08:35.882 --> 08:38.384
I'm gonna stay in contact
with all the people I've met,

08:38.484 --> 08:42.822
obviously, because they're
some of my best friends now.

08:42.889 --> 08:44.090
Nice meeting you, too.

08:44.190 --> 08:45.258
You got so much better
at ping-pong.

08:45.358 --> 08:47.760
I know.
Thanks to you guys.

08:49.161 --> 08:50.830
It was awesome
meeting you finally.

08:58.704 --> 09:00.573
You gonna be okay?

09:00.673 --> 09:02.942
Yeah.

09:03.042 --> 09:04.210
Okay.

09:04.277 --> 09:06.445
You can come help me pack.

09:06.546 --> 09:07.880
Okay. Perfect.

09:07.947 --> 09:09.348
It hurts.

09:09.415 --> 09:12.118
It hurts me so, so much

09:12.218 --> 09:14.954
because
we were falling more and more

09:15.054 --> 09:17.189
for each other every single day.

09:18.257 --> 09:21.761
Let's see what...

09:21.861 --> 09:23.429
Are you crying? Dude,
I told you not to cry.

09:23.529 --> 09:26.566
I'm trying not to.
That's why I couldn't say more.

09:26.632 --> 09:30.536
We connected like no other,
you know?

09:30.603 --> 09:33.940
I felt a really
strong connection between us.

09:34.040 --> 09:37.043
Hey, Alex,
please don't get so sad.

09:37.109 --> 09:38.477
Okay?

09:38.578 --> 09:41.414
I'm not.
I'm not.

09:41.480 --> 09:43.983
Cool. 'Cause you know I can't
handle emotions like that.

09:44.083 --> 09:45.651
I know.

09:49.822 --> 09:51.657
It's hard.

09:52.959 --> 09:54.493
I'm just --

09:54.594 --> 09:55.561
I'm sad.

09:55.628 --> 09:56.729
I don't even know
what to say.

09:56.796 --> 09:58.631
I don't have
anything to say, actually.

09:58.731 --> 10:00.066
Mm.

10:00.132 --> 10:02.068
What if I do
a little jiggy?

10:02.134 --> 10:04.503
But we live really far
from each other,

10:04.604 --> 10:07.006
so, you know, reality hits.

10:07.106 --> 10:10.009
And even though I don't like
to admit it,

10:10.109 --> 10:16.949
this probably is it
for Noah and me.

10:17.016 --> 10:18.584
Yeah.

10:18.651 --> 10:21.187
And I think that
that's hard to process.

10:21.287 --> 10:26.325
Noah and I are at such
different stages in our lives.

10:26.425 --> 10:28.694
Want to come in here?

10:28.794 --> 10:33.032
18 and 22
are very different ages.

10:35.801 --> 10:38.537
But maybe 26 and 30.

10:38.638 --> 10:40.172
There we go.

10:41.440 --> 10:44.377
We're getting in the car,
bro.

10:44.477 --> 10:46.612
Noah:
I got to learn a lot about Alex,

10:46.679 --> 10:51.017
but I'm sorry that we didn't
get more time together.

10:51.117 --> 10:54.120
We didn't know this was gonna
happen. It was really cool.

10:54.186 --> 10:56.889
It was a friendship
that just turned romantic.

10:56.989 --> 10:58.991
And those are always the best.

11:01.027 --> 11:04.230
I'm pretty sad
about leaving her behind.

11:04.330 --> 11:06.499
I know she is, too.

11:08.234 --> 11:12.238
But I can't imagine
not seeing her again.

11:33.025 --> 11:37.263
Do you have any plans
for any weekends in September

11:37.363 --> 11:39.565
that you can think of
off the top of your head?

11:39.665 --> 11:41.067
Not off the top of my head.

11:41.167 --> 11:42.768
And whenever you're coming,
I'll make sure it's free.

11:42.868 --> 11:45.104
Well, you know, I have to see
what works for Myles.

11:45.204 --> 11:46.439
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:46.539 --> 11:48.274
But then I'll tell you.

11:48.374 --> 11:51.343
And I will obviously be talking
to you on a daily basis,

11:51.410 --> 11:52.878
so I'll let you know.

11:52.945 --> 11:55.448
I mean, is that cool with you,
or is that too much?

11:55.548 --> 11:56.782
That's too much.

11:56.882 --> 11:58.718
That's too much.
I'm joking.

11:58.784 --> 12:02.021
I'm gonna be missing you
like crazy.

12:02.088 --> 12:03.956
All right?
You make that face.

12:04.056 --> 12:06.392
But you'll see.

12:06.459 --> 12:07.793
It's your fault.

12:07.893 --> 12:09.628
What's my fault?

12:09.729 --> 12:12.298
That I care for you
so deeply.

12:12.398 --> 12:14.300
How?

12:14.400 --> 12:15.468
Mm...

12:17.136 --> 12:18.437
- Oh, hey.
- Hi, Nicole.

12:18.537 --> 12:20.206
Hi, everyone.
Good evening.

12:20.272 --> 12:22.208
Hello, hello.

12:22.274 --> 12:23.743
Wow, everyone looks lovely.

12:23.809 --> 12:24.944
Thank you.

12:25.044 --> 12:29.315
So I have four cards
for four lovely ladies.

12:29.415 --> 12:31.217
And we just --

12:31.283 --> 12:32.451
Oh, I'm, like --
I'm counting.

12:32.551 --> 12:33.886
I'm like, "One, two,
three, four."

12:33.953 --> 12:35.821
Thank you. Nice.

12:35.921 --> 12:37.556
Yay. Thanks.

12:37.623 --> 12:39.091
- There we go.
- Thank you.

12:39.158 --> 12:41.127
You're welcome.
There you go.

12:41.227 --> 12:43.662
All right.
Have a good night, everyone.

12:43.763 --> 12:46.132
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

12:46.232 --> 12:48.467
Can we open? Okay.

12:48.567 --> 12:50.936
Oh.
We all got one.

12:51.003 --> 12:52.972
